x4freetext: Measurement of energy spectrum and average number
Time-of-flight method for measurement of prompt
neutron spectra used . TOF base 50 cm. Time resolution
Neutron spectra of investigated isotopes were measured
intermittently with measurement of U235 fission neutron
spectrum by thermal neutrons. U-235 spectrum was
supposed to be proportional to sqrt(E)*exp(-E/T) with
T=1.29 MeV. Parameters of U-235 spectrum:
fission neutrons at fission by thermal neutrons .
NU is given in Subents 002-007 as MONIT.

100 mm diameter, 30 mm long, connected with FEU-63,
Protected by 15 mm lead layer. Detector threshold was
constantly controls by 59.6 keV gammas of Am-241.
Neutron detector efficiency dependence from energy was
determined by U-235 neutron spectrum, taking into
Background of random coincidence was taken into account
Units were corrected NO-DIM -> PRT/FIS for NU. AKE->KE.
BIB and COMMON information was added.
